headline: Anal Cancer Market Research Report 2025-2035 with Competitive Profiles of Incyte, BioMimetix, Bristol Myers Squibb, and AstraZeneca
summary: Anal cancer is a rare yet increasing cancer linked primarily to high-risk HPV strains such as HPV-16 and HPV-18. Key risk factors include weakened immune systems, age over 50, and high-risk sexual behaviors. Symptoms encompass rectal bleeding, pain, and changes in bowel habits. Early detection through HPV vaccination and screenings is vital, yet challenges persist due to limited early detection protocols.
